Norway, Denmark to Cooperate on Chalk Field Recovery

-- B y   M a r i a n n e   S t i g s e t
-- 
2011-10-18T08:43:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-17/norway-denmark-to-cooperate-on-enhanced-chalk-field-recovery.html
     (Corrects currency conversion in second paragraph in story
published Oct. 17.)  The Norwegian Petroleum Directorate,
the Danish Energy Agency and 10 oil companies will cooperate on
research and development and share experience to improve
recovery from chalk fields off Norway and Denmark, the Norwegian
agency said in an e-mailed statement today.  The oil companies participating in the project are  BP Plc (BP/) ,
 ConocoPhillips (COP) , the Danish North Sea Fund, Dong Energy A/S,  Eni
SpA (ENI) , Hess Corp., AP Moller-MÃ¦rsk A/S,  Statoil ASA (STL) ,  Royal Dutch
Shell Plc (RDSA)  and  Total SA. (FP)  They are contributing up to 2 million
kroner ($373,000) annually as of 2012, initially for a period of
three years, the NPD said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marianne Stigset at 
 mstigset@bloomberg.net  